<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post155804"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Anonimus Clerique</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Jul 2002<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 13</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Pre-PoP we used a lot of heal rotations that required hotkeys like:<br />
<br />
/g Complete Heal &#123; %T }<br />
/pause 20<br />
/g Name heal now<br />
<br />
When channels were introduced we made use of those for a while, but the constant crashes, lag, and bugs caused us to stop rotating in them.  We used /auction a lot - yes it's a public channel but people can easily filter out the spam.<br />
<br />
Since PoP our angry dwarf guildleader has been on a mission to take away heal rotations (hey they're the easy way to play the game, let's be honest).  We honed our skills and did most of the planar bosses without any rotations.  When we have to rotate, something like this is preferable:<br />
<br />
/ooc < # > Complete Heal &#123; %T } -- Name is next<br />
<br />
No pause, and only one message.  The # is, as someone mentioned, to keep a visible order.  We got rid of virtually all pauses in rotations because counting in your head is important - it adds flexibility.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Anonimus Clerique<br />
Tholuxe Paells<br />
Malus Imperium</font></p></p>
